#principles for context engineering

1. If you’re an agent-builder, ensure your agent’s every action is informed by the context of all relevant decisions made by other parts of the system
- Ideally, every action would just see everything else.

A. Unfortunately, this is not always possible due to 
- limited context windows and 
- practical tradeoffs, and 
- you may need to decide what level of complexity you are willing to take on for the level of reliability you aim for.


